  "number": "1.2",
  "title": "Explore",
  "body": " Explore    Explore: Scientific Notation     Reinforce your ability to convert between standard and scientific notation and interpret the meaning of powers of ten in real-world and scientific contexts.      This worksheet is designed to help you explore the concept of scientific notation in physics.         The influenza virus can have a diameter of about 0.000000099 meters. Convert 0.000000099 to scientific notation.    The decimal point would need to move to the right by 8 places.         To write 0.000000099 in scientific notation, move the decimal point eight places to the right to place it after the first nonzero digit. This gives \"9.9\". Since the decimal moved right by eight places, the exponent on 10 is -8.  So, .        A strand of human hair is about 0.00007 meters in diameter. Convert 0.00007 to scientific notation.    The decimal point would need to move to the right by 5 places.         To write 0.00007 in scientific notation, move the decimal point five places to the right to place it after the first nonzero digit. This gives \"7.0\". Since the decimal moved right by five places, the exponent on 10 is -5.  So, .        A grain of sand can be about 0.0012 meters in diameter. Convert 0.0012 to scientific notation.    The decimal point would need to move to the right by 3 places.         To write 0.0012 in scientific notation, move the decimal point three places to the right to place it after the first nonzero digit. This gives \"1.2\". Since the decimal moved right by three places, the exponent on 10 is -3.  So, .        An average adult human might be about 1.75 meters tall. Convert 1.75 to scientific notation.    The decimal point would need to move to the left by 0 places.         To write 1.75 in scientific notation, the decimal is already after the first nonzero digit, so we don’t need to move it. That means the exponent on 10 is 0.  So, .        The Empire State Building in New York City is about meters tall. Convert to standard notation.    A positive exponent means move the decimal to the right. Move it 2 places to the right.    381     means move the decimal point 2 places to the right: .  So, .        Mount Everest is approximately meters tall. Convert to standard notation.    Move the decimal point 3 places to the right.    8850     means move the decimal 3 places to the right: .  So, .        The Earth's diameter is about meters. Convert to standard notation.    Move the decimal 7 places to the right.    12,700,000     means move the decimal 7 places to the right: .  So, .        The average distance from Earth to the Sun is about meters. Convert to standard notation.    Move the decimal 11 places to the right.    149,600,000,000     means move the decimal 11 places to the right: .  So, .        About how many orders of magnitude larger is a human compared to a grain of sand? Use questions and to help.     Compare the exponents: vs. . How many powers of ten apart are they?    3    The exponent for the human's height is 0, and for the grain of sand it is -3. The difference is .  So, a human is approximately 3 orders of magnitude larger than a grain of sand. This means the human is about times taller than the grain of sand.  In other words, if you stacked 1,000 grains of sand end to end, they would reach about the height of one person!        About how many orders of magnitude larger is a human compared to an influenza virus? Use questions and to help.     Compare the exponents: vs. . How many powers of ten apart are they?    8    The exponent for the human's height is 0, and for the virus it is -8. The difference is .  So, a human is approximately 8 orders of magnitude larger than the influenza virus. This means the human is about times taller than the virus.  In other words, if you stacked 100,000,000 viruses end to end, they would reach about the height of one person!      "
